caption: I visit red mango like 1-2 times a week and always get their delicious Acai bowl. I ordered delivery from them via Doordash and got (among other things) their Chocolate Hazelnut Banana Berry Acai bowl. I noticed that the item description included pumpkin seed granola, which I have a hard time eating, so I told them in the comments and asked if they would be able to substitute the granola with whatever fruit they might have available. I received a bowl full of fruit of all kinds (the quality of the fruit was wonderful, very fresh!). They really went above and beyond my expectations and I am so grateful to the staff for their amazing customer service. Thank you so much, and I absolutely cannot wait to order from here again!

Haha okay, to begin with, I'm a huge ice cream/fro-yo eater. I was feeling the craving for something sweet and cold, so obviously ice cream was my first thought. I was hoping that Red Mango would do it for me but it seriously didn't. This Red Mango is quite small and not the cleanest. The cups and bowls are in the back of the store. When we entered, there was no one at the counter to greet us. We got our cups of fro-yo and went to the counter to pay and get toppings. We had to wait there while the employee was on her phone and doing other things.  Since it was a little breezy outside, we decided to eat there. While we were there, the employee was making an order to go, and while doing so, dropped a spoon on the ground. She then proceeded to put that spoon back into the pile of other spoons that were there. ... Gross.

We went to Red Mango based on G+ suggestion. My friend had been looking for a specific dessert which was referenced on the menu. Unfortunately the strawberry shortcake wasn't a full-on dessert but instead a flavor of milkshake. We decided on a cookie sandwich instead. It was tasty but a little pricy. I knew it was popular so I cannot complain about the wait time on a Saturday night in July. I will complain, however, that the restroom was out of order and the staff was in an extreme rush to move us along. Overall- a good experience- but probably not enough to go out of the way to return.

Everyone loves Red Mango, but if you're expecting the same quality service from this location, well, don't. The workers are unfriendly and weird. Their flavors are more of "Red velvet cupcake" and almost none of the original flavors such as pomegranate or regular. And, the biggest downside, is that to try a flavor, you have to let the workers fill one of those tiny cups FOR YOU with whatever amount they decide and hand it to you. It's usually dripping on their hands, and it makes for a very unsanitary situation. I understand that people abuse samples, but would it be the biggest deal to just continue to hide the sample cups behind the counter and hand the customer one when they want a sample?

Then she was putting a drop in the cup and gave it to me. I am used that you get a hand full sampling cups if you want as soon as you enter the shop and then you can sample as much as you like by self service.
